      "writtenOn": "2020-11-02T23:59:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "no and no.\n\nFor code here, my comment in code above is accurate.\n\n\nToday, in CQDaemon:\nIf 0 or 1 match, obvious.\nIf 2 match AND 1 is fallback, choose the other one (ie ignore fallback group)\nElse: CL isn\u0027t considered (this is similar if 2 *projects* watch the same ref\n\n\nNote that if 2 different LUCI projects, managed by 2 diff CQDaemon processes, each watch the same host/repo/ref,\nthen each Daemon will be processing the CL from such a ref.\n\n\nSo, in the CV, we\u0027ll do better:\ngobmap.Lookup() returns set(\n  select_groups(project) for project in luci_projects\n)\n\nwhere select_groups(project) takes care of fallback the same way as individual CQDaemon.\n\n\n\nThe caller of \n   groups :\u003d gobmap.Lookup()\nwill then proceed iff len(groups) \u003d\u003d 1.\nIf len() \u003d\u003d 2, then it\u0027ll emit errors, and I guess the error will be different depending on whether groups are from the same or different LUCI project.",
